          <h3>1. Create an Ethereum Wallet on MetaMask: </br> <img src = "/metamask.JPG" width = "800" height = "250"> </h3>
          <p>
              1a. Setting up your account is easy.  In order to create an account, you will need an Ethereum wallet to buy and sell documents.  This is made easy with MetaMask, a simple and easy chrome plug-in for handling Ethereum Wallets.  Click <a href="https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/metamask/nkbihfbeogaeaoehlefnkodbefgpgknn?hl=en" target="_blank">HERE</a> to install Metamask. Remember your password, and store your recovery info somewhere safe.
          </p>
          <p>
              1b. Once you've registered, you'll need to configure the testnet setings to the Rinkeby testnet. To do this, click the testnet icon in the upper left corner of MetaMask, and select the Ropsten testnet.
          </p>
